By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) –   Senator representing Osun West senatorial district, Ademola Adeleke, has won the governorship ticket of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) in Osun state with 7 votes difference. The senator defeated his closest challenger, Akin Ogunbiyi, to emerge the flagbearer of the PDP in the September 22 governorship election.  Adeleke won by a close margin, securing 1569 votes while Ogunbiyi had 1562. With the result, Senator Adeleke won the PDP governorship ticket with 7 votes.